.TH AGENT-HOOK-SESSION-START 1 "2026-06-30" "agentguard" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
agent-hook-session-start \- emit startup context for an agent session
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B agent-hook-session-start
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B agent-hook-session-start
reads a session-start hook JSON payload from standard input, reports repository
context, warns on local environment issues such as high disk usage, and asks
Hive Memory for startup context when
.BR hm (1)
is installed and configured.
.PP
When a session is launched from
.BR $HOME ,
AgentGuard treats that as no active project instead of passing the home
directory as a project hint.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Startup context was emitted or no context was available.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR agent-hook-prompt-submit (1),
.BR hm (1)
